                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-26T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 26, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. Your despatch No. 1430, March 11, and telegram No. 463, April 23, 1 p.m., in
                    regard to the Hai Ho conservancy. You are authorized to reply in terms similar
                    to those of the proposed draft quoted in paragraph 2 of your telegram under
                    reference provided the representatives of Britain and most other most interested
                    powers do so.<note n="32" xml:id="d752fn32">The American note, dated May 6,
                        1932, followed identic notes from the British, Netherlands, and Spanish
                        Legations and preceded those of the French and Japanese Legations
                        (893.811/855, 858).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
